    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup is anchored by **Gunnar Henderson** today, who presents our highest ceiling at 79.79. He draws a favorable matchup against S. Smith, benefiting from a +14% platoon edge and, crucially, a slow opposing pitcher who creates an opportunistic environment for his elite stolen base potential. **Josh Lowe** (71.68) and **Kyle Tucker** (67.98) represent the secondary tier of high-efficiency plays. **Josh Lowe** is a prime candidate against Reynaldo L\u00f3pez, where a massive 19% boost from the SP skill profile and an favorable dynamic platoon shift propel him well into the strong-start category. Meanwhile, **Kyle Tucker** remains a consistent anchor despite Gausman\u2019s presence, buoyed by strong underlying xwOBA metrics. \n\nThe optimizer\u2019s most difficult exclusion was **Miguel Vargas**, who finished just outside the starting nine with a 50.02 score. While his projection benefited from a #3 order spot, his overall efficiency metrics were slightly outpaced by the park-adjusted profiles of **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Andy Pages**. We are closely monitoring the status of **Drake Baldwin**, **Josh Lowe**, and **Nolan Schanuel**; as of now, their scores are contingent on assumed lineup positions. Should these players fall lower in their respective batting orders, we will see immediate regression in their daily scoring output. \n\nWe are exercising caution with **Jackson Merrill**, whose 51.93 score is suppressed by a difficult encounter with Skenes. While his dynamic platoon edge is significant, the combination of an elite catcher\u2019s pop time and Skenes's high skill ceiling makes him a marginal start. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** faces an uphill battle against Yamamoto. Despite his talent, his score is tempered by a significant SP skill penalty (-16%) and a negative platoon shift, reinforcing the need to weigh raw talent against today\u2019s specific matchup variables. Keep a close watch on **Jordan Westburg** on the IL; his absence remains the primary constraint on our bench depth.",
